10/11/2008
JERUSALEM, Israel -- Five Croatian tourists suffered serious injuries, while another 15 incurred minor injuries, in a bus accident in Israel late on Saturday (November 8th).
Police say a preliminary investigation suggests the crash was the bus driver's fault.
In all, 48 passengers were aboard the vehicle, bound from Nazareth and Galilee.
(MIA, HRT, Jerusalem Post - 08/11/08)
